{
  "texts": [
    "Yet you have something we grounded learners don't and cannot have: your LLM-scale bag of words, propositions, contexts, and your computational power over those.",
    "That's something we grounded mortals can only have at local-, not LLM-scale.",
    "Bottom-Up Nature of Grounding: I \"understand\" your point that grounding, whether direct (sensorimotor) or indirect (verbal), is inherently a bottom-up process.",
    "In this framework, the grounding of any concept depends on the already established grounding of its constituent elements.",
    "When learning the referent of a content word through verbal means, all defining content words within the explanation must themselves be grounded, either directly or indirectly."
  ]
}